column21: Dr. Mir Jawad Zar Khan is a senior orthopedist, orthopedic surgeon and joint replacement and spine surgeon in Attapur, Hyderabad and has an experience of 21 years in these fields. Dr. Mir Jawad Zar Khan practices at Germanten Hospital, which is a hospital for advanced orthopedics & trauma in Attapur, Hyderabad. He has done Masters that is M.S (Orthopaedics) from Osmania University, Hyderabad and M.Ch Orthopedics from Usaim, Seychelles. He has done a fellowship in arthroplasty in world renowned orthopedic institute in Munich Germany where he has worked with international experts in joint replacements surgeries. He was awarded best outgoing postgraduate with highest marks in Andhra Pradesh state. He has undergone extensive training in trauma & orthopedics during his post graduation. He has further training in complicated fractures, joint replacements, spine surgery & arthroscopic ACL/PCL reconstruction, meniscal repair surgeries at prestigious Osmania General Government Hospital which is a tertiary care referral center in Andhra Pradesh & Telangana State during his senior residency. He has undergone advanced training in joint replacements as part of his fellowship program at prestigious Institutes of Lilavati, Beach Candy Hospital Mumbai & Max Hospital Delhi with International experts in the above fields. He has worked & undergone extensive training in joint replacements of knee, hip, shoulder, arthroscopic surgeries, spine surgeries during his fellowship program in Munich Germany with world-renowned experts. Dr.Jawad is an expert in computer navigation joint replacement surgery and has performed large series of navigated hip and knee replacement surgeries in Germany.  Doctor can be contacted round the clock for any advice on orthopedic problems & fractures. He is a active member of Indian Orthopedic Association, Orthopedic Surgeons Society Of A.P, Indian Medical Association (IMA), (IGOF) Indo-German Orthopedic Foundation, Society,  Internationale De Chirurgie Orthopedic Et De Traumatologie (Sicot), International Society Of Orthopedic Surgery & Traumatology, International Cartilage Research Society, Indian Arthroplasty Association, International Society For Knowledge For Surgeons On Arthroscopy And Arthroplasty And International Society Of Arthroscopy, Knee Surgery And Orthopedic Sports Medicine. Dr. Jawad had a brilliant academic career all through his studies. He has presented research papers & articles & participated in numerous conferences in India & Internationally. Dr. Jawad is highly interested in research-oriented activities & keeps updating his knowledge by attending various orthopedic conferences & workshops which have added to his skill & expertise. The doctor has extensive years of experience in accurately diagnosing Orthopedic conditions with fewer investigations & offering cost effective treatment. Dr.Jawad is not only a competent surgeon but also an excellent clinician with a soft spoken & humane approach towards his patients. A doctor has treated numerous patients with complicated trauma.He has treated many elderly patients with fractures taking care of all their medical needs.  Dr. Jawads Motto in doing joint replacement is to make it a successful surgery with the fastest recovery & early mobility with taking into account all aspects of patients physical & mental health. He discusses in detail with each patient all aspects of the surgery, implants used, costs & prognosis, etc. A doctor has treated many sportsmen of state & National ranking who visit him frequently for sports injuries. Germanten hospital is a setup by Dr. Jawad to provide orthopedic & trauma care with all latest equipment's & highly advanced laminar airflow operation theaters for total infection control.  Dr. Jawad's team comprises of dedicated doctors, operation theater staff, physiotherapists & support staff who work in tandem & whose respective services complement each other for the total recovery & satisfaction of the patients. Doctor can be contacted round the clock for any advice on orthopedic problems & fractures. 24hrs ambulance service is provided free of cost. The hospital has a cashless facility for all insurance health cards & state govt employees. The aarogyasree facility is available.

column21: Dr. Balaraju Naidu stands as a beacon of excellence in the field of orthopedic surgery, particularly renowned for his expertise in Robotic Joint Replacements. With an international training background and a wealth of experience across countries such as the UK, Italy, Germany, and France, Dr. Naidu has emerged as a globally acclaimed  Chief Robotic Orthopedic Surgeon.  *Educational Achievements:* A graduate of MS (Ortho) and MBBS from Gandhi Hospital, Gandhi Medical College, Dr. Naidu holds a DNB-Orthopaedics degree. His pursuit of knowledge extended to an Advanced Management Program in Healthcare from the prestigious Indian School of Business. Notably, he received the Prathibha Award for securing top marks in SSC, underscoring his academic brilliance.  *Awards and Recognitions:* Dr. Balaraju Naidu's outstanding contributions to orthopedic surgery have earned him numerous accolades. Notable among these are 1) The Best Doctor Award from Sri. Roshiah, Former CM and Governor in 2018. 2) The HYBIZ Media Award presented by Sri. KTR, Former Honorable Minister for IT and E&C in 2021. 3)Three Best Rated Award in 2022, the Nationwide Award for the most promising healthcare professional in 2022, 4) The Best Orthopedic Doctor Award from Sri Harish Rao Garu, Former Honorable Minister for Health Telangana in 2022. 5) The APJ Abdul Kalam Health Excellence Award in 2023 and 6) The Times Health Excellence Award in Service Excellence in Robotic Orthopedic Surgery in 2023 further solidify his stature in the medical community.  *International and National Fellowships:* Dr. Naidu's pursuit of excellence led him to undertake fellowships in various countries. Under the mentorship of esteemed surgeons, he completed fellowships in Robotic Joint Replacement Surgery in Italy, Hip and Knee Replacement Surgery in Milan, Computer Navigation Replacement Surgery in Germany, Peri Prosthetic Fracture Fixation in France, and Arthroplasty and Arthroscopy in the United Kingdom.  *Professional Associations and Publications:* Actively involved in research and clinical audit activities, Dr. Naidu has contributed significantly to the field with publications and presentations at state, national, and international conferences. His membership in prestigious organizations such as SICOT, ISKSAA, IOA, ISH KS, TOSA, and TCOS reflects his commitment to advancing orthopedic knowledge.  *Areas of Interest:* While Dr. Balaraju Naidu's primary focus lies in Robotic Joint Replacement Surgeries, he is proficient in trauma, knee, hip, and upper limb procedures. His dedication to staying at the forefront of orthopedic advancements is evident in his continuous efforts to acquire and implement the latest techniques. Dr. Naidu not only practices cutting-edge orthopedics but also advocates for preventive care and health fitness, embodying a holistic approach to patient well-being.              He graduated  MS(Orth) and MBBS from Gandhi Hospital, Gandhi Medical College. He also passed DNB-Orthopaedics. While his main interest remains in Robotic and Computer Navigation Joint Replacement Surgeries, also performs all Trauma, Knee, Hip and Upper Limb procedures.

column21: Dr. Sandeep Prasad is a reputed orthopedic surgeon from Health Valley Hospital, Kondapur. He has over 20 years of experience as a Trauma & Orthopaedics Specialist and a Joint Replacement Surgeon.  After completing his MBBS from Osmania medical college, he completed his Master of Surgery in orthopedics. Post that, he went to the UK to pursue his further studies. He has taken up many medical courses and has successfully achieved MCh Ortho, MRCS RCSENG from London, FRCS in Trauma and Ortho, Advanced Trauma Life Support (UK), Association of the Study of Internal Fixation AO (USA), and DIP(OXFORD).  Armed with such valued medical degrees from such reputed institutes, he has served 17 years of his career in various healthcare institutes across UK. To name a few, he was associated with Homerton University Hospital (London) for 6 years, Walsgrave University Hospital (Coventry, Europe), Worcester Royal Infirmary (UK), Solihull NHS Trust (UK), Derbyshire Royal infirmary (UK), etc. He has also served at NHS, England in various honorable positions. For a brief time, he has worked at St Barnes Jewish Hospital in the USA, Royal Orthopaedic Hospital Birmingham, Queen Elizabeth Hospital , Nuffield Hospital, Sandwell Dudley NHS trust, etc  During his service, he has worked with several highly experienced orthopaedic consultants and has been trained in many complex orthopedic procedures. He has taken hands-on training in trauma care and has practised the same. He always keeps himself updated in the latest advancements in the medical world so that he can provide the best care to his patients.  Some of his specialties include complex trauma surgeries, Knee and Hip Replacements, Revision Joint Replacement Surgeries, etc. He has participated in many educational workshops where he has involved himself to educate his juniors and learn from his seniors and to stay updated on the latest techniques of surgery, treatment, and recovery.  Even though he is primarily a surgeon, he always believes in a comprehensive approach to his treatment. However, even when they do require surgery, he insists on very mindful pre-surgery take up and post-surgery care.  Because of this way of approach to his patients, added value to his care. In 2018, he finally moved back to India to use his skills to serve his own country. After initially working with Apollo Hospitals for a while, he has joined Health Valley Hospitals as an Orthopedic Surgeon.  To receive treatment under his care, visit him in Health Valley Hospitals, Kondapur where he works full time. Doctor will be available On-Call after 9 pm also for emergency services.

column21: Dr B.Chakradhar Reddy is an Allopath Orthopedist, Shoulder Surgeon Joint Replacement Surgeon  at SLG Hospitals Nizampet,  Dr. B.Chakradhar Reddy is a true genius in his field. He has not only been great in his academics, but has also proved his worth in his hands-on experience at a very early stage of his career. From then on for 17 years, his expert hands have only gained exponential excellence in various orthopaedic surgical fields  EDUCATION: Dr. B.Chakradhar Reddy’s potential as a medical expert first surfaced when he secured a rank in the top 500 in Engineering Agricultural and Medical Common Entrance Test (EAMCET), which is undoubtedly an extremely competitive and popular exam in all over India. It came with its unique perks – a chance to study in the best colleges. Dr. B.Chakradhar Reddy takes pride in graduating from Sri Venkateswara Medical College, Tirupati. He completed his MBBS course in 1998.  From the same college, he took up the course of Master of Surgery in Orthopaedics and most-deservingly, secured the 16th rank in the state when he passed the course in 2002.  FOREIGN PURSUITS: Dr. B.Chakradhar Reddy has, till now, been the best at whatever he does in the field of orthopaedics. So, it’s no wonder that when he was looking for further studies, he would look for the best place to do the same. He secured a place in the best University even in a foreign land – Ninewells Hospital & Medical School. Ninewells Hospital & Medical School comes from University of Dundee, Scotland. It was and still is one of the best institutes for medical studies in the world. In 2006, Dr. Reddy completed his M.Ch. in Orthopaedics from the said institute.  After his higher studies in Scotland in 2006, he had the opportunity of taking some additional training in the UK. Dr. Reddy is not the kind of person who believes in luck, but he is the kind of person who believes in seizing every opportunity he gets to better himself. He went through some hard and rigorous training sessions in Edinburgh and Glasgow, UK. He has cleared the prestigious Membership of the Royal Colleges of Surgeons of Great Britain and Ireland (MRCS) and Fellowship of the Royal Colleges of Surgeons (FRCS).  His academic credit does not end here. He even went forward to pursue post-FRCS shoulder fellowship at Kirkcaldy under the supervision of world-renowned doctors, Dr. Sunil Sharma and Dr. Robert D. Cook. He trained his skilful hands under the guidance of Dr. Richard Pickard and Dr Andrew clarification require as a Joint Replacement Fellow and in Shoulder Replacment fellowship in Golden Jubilee National Hospital, near Glasgow, Scotland.   Dr. Chakradhar is a well known Orthopedic Shoulder Surgeon and one of the British expats in Hyderabad, of Indian Origin. moved to India in April 2014.  Dr. Reddy has a reputation for being empathetic. His patients don’t shy away from telling how wonderful treatment they get from his service. What makes his treatment better than his competitors is that he explains the issue to the patient in a way that they can understand both the severity and the treatment clearly. A clear mind always has a positive attitude towards the doctor and his work, which, undoubtedly, contributes in yielding a better result at the end.    B.Chakradhar Reddy has a bigger vision, and he has already started working on it. Alongside worked at Apollo Kondapur as a Full time Senior Orthopedic Consultant till  May 2019. he also had his own clinic at Madinaguda, Hyderabad – Dr. Chakri’s  Orthopedic Clinic.  In the short time that he has opened his clinic, it has already earned a lot of goodwill from the profile of the doctor who runs it – Dr. Reddy, of course! In his own words, his aim is “to provide my patients with the highest quality healthcare.” He is dedicated to the newest advancements and keeps the clinic updated with the latest healthcare technologies.
